    "comment": "Rationale: Authors used MAPKK antisera and detected MAPKK immunoreactivity in PSD fractions prepared from rat cerebral cortex, hippocampus and cerebellum. MAPKK is also present in all analyzed fractions (soluble, synaptosome and synaptic plasma membrane). However, MAPKK immunoreactivity increased following synaptogenesis (3 weeks after birth) in the synaptosomal and PSD fraction which suggests that MAPKK functions in the synapse.. Experimental description: From M&M:\n- Subcellular fractions were obtained from Wistar rats.\n- Literal: \"Anti-MAPKK monoclonal antibody was produced as reported (Kosako et al., 1994)\"\nInformation found in Kosako et al., 1994: \"We produced an anti-MAPKK antibody by immunizing mice with a bacterially expressed fusion protein between glutathione-S-transferase (GST) and Xenopus MAPKK.\"",
